extracted_text: (h) Lot Coverage. Accessory structures to a residential use shall not have a ground floor area which exceeds 50 percent of the ground floor area of the principal building.
llm_outputs.rationale: The extracted text provides a clear statement of the maximum lot coverage for accessory structures in relation to the principal building, which is 50 percent of the ground floor area of the principal building. This satisfies the definition of max_lot_coverage as it pertains to the maximum lot coverage of buildings for primary use and all accessory structures.
